  <mainDescription>&lt;h3>&#xD;
    Description&#xD;
&lt;/h3>&#xD;
&lt;p>&#xD;
    Predictability is the degree to which&amp;nbsp;a project&amp;nbsp;team can accurately forecast successful project completion.&#xD;
    Improving predictability also refers to the ability to reduce uncertainties in the project in order to increase&#xD;
    estimation accuracy. Understanding the&amp;nbsp;uncertainly in&amp;nbsp;a project reduces the probability of project failure,&#xD;
    because the team is aware of potential problems.&amp;nbsp;&#xD;
&lt;/p>&#xD;
&lt;p>&#xD;
    Improving&amp;nbsp;predictability helps&amp;nbsp;the team produce a realistic plan that can be executed.&amp;nbsp; Teams that lack&#xD;
    predictability will not be able to accurately plan their release,&amp;nbsp;prioritize the features to be delivered,&amp;nbsp;or&#xD;
    determine the quality of the product.&amp;nbsp;&#xD;
&lt;/p>&#xD;
&lt;h3>&#xD;
    Strategies&#xD;
&lt;/h3>&#xD;
&lt;p>&#xD;
    The following strategies help improve Predictability:&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&#xD;
&lt;/p>&#xD;
&lt;ul>&#xD;
    &lt;li>&#xD;
        &lt;a class=&quot;elementLink&quot;&#xD;
        href=&quot;./../../practice.tech.syseng.common.extend_relm-ibm/customcategories/improve_process_governance_and_compliance_9F7B88FF.html&quot;&#xD;
         guid=&quot;_U0Z4MODCEeGvfsngvHRPbg&quot;>Strategy: Improve Process Governance and Compliance&lt;/a>&#xD;
    &lt;/li>&#xD;
    &lt;li style=&quot;LIST-STYLE-TYPE: none&quot;>&#xD;
        &lt;ul>&#xD;
            &lt;li>&#xD;
                Set up a standard process that can be repeated from one project to the next&#xD;
            &lt;/li>&#xD;
            &lt;li>&#xD;
                Mature the process to better manage development activities and forecast what needs to be done.&#xD;
            &lt;/li>&#xD;
            &lt;li>&#xD;
                Increase ability to understand organizational performance&amp;nbsp;in order to&amp;nbsp;tailor, adopt and enact&#xD;
                appropriate processes&#xD;
            &lt;/li>&#xD;
            &lt;li>&#xD;
                Indicators&#xD;
            &lt;/li>&#xD;
            &lt;li style=&quot;LIST-STYLE-TYPE: none&quot;>&#xD;
                &lt;ul>&#xD;
                    &lt;li>&#xD;
                        No process standard across organization&#xD;
                    &lt;/li>&#xD;
                    &lt;li>&#xD;
                        Inconsistent adoption or no adoption&#xD;
                    &lt;/li>&#xD;
                    &lt;li>&#xD;
                        No criteria to understand how to&amp;nbsp;tailor the process&#xD;
                    &lt;/li>&#xD;
                    &lt;li>&#xD;
                        No clear roles and job descriptions&#xD;
                    &lt;/li>&#xD;
                    &lt;li>&#xD;
                        Inability to&amp;nbsp;harvest past experiences to improve the process&lt;br />&#xD;
                    &lt;/li>&#xD;
                &lt;/ul>&#xD;
            &lt;/li>&#xD;
        &lt;/ul>&#xD;
    &lt;/li>&#xD;
&lt;/ul></mainDescription>
</org.eclipse.epf.uma:ContentDescription>
